                    ('The ideal ratio of quotation to commentary in an AP® Language essay is approximately:', ['More commentary than quotation — at least two lines of commentary for every line of quotation', 'Quotation and commentary are equal in length throughout the essay', 'Mostly quotation with brief commentary labels identifying device names', 'Every quotation must be exactly one sentence in length']),
                    ('In the AP® Language rubric, the evidence and commentary row rewards:', ['Selecting relevant evidence and explaining how it specifically supports the line of reasoning', 'Including the most quotations from the provided text', 'Using evidence from sources outside the provided passage', 'Summarizing the author\'s argument accurately']),
