                    ('A "dropped quotation" is problematic because:', ['It appears without introduction or attribution, disrupting flow and leaving the reader confused about its source', 'Quotations without signal phrases automatically fail AP® rubric requirements', 'It places quotation marks incorrectly around the borrowed text', 'Direct quotation should never appear in an analytical essay']),
                    ('Accurate paraphrase requires:', ['Genuinely restating the meaning in the writer\'s own phrasing and sentence structure, not just substituting synonyms', 'Changing only the subject of the sentence from the original', 'Using the same sentence structure as the original but replacing key words', 'Placing paraphrased material in quotation marks']),
