                    ('An effective concession acknowledges:', ['The validity of part of the opposing argument while maintaining the overall position', 'That the writer was completely wrong about an element of the argument', 'That the topic is too complex to reach any conclusion', 'Every possible objection before the argument can proceed']),
                    ('A rebuttal following a concession should:', ['Explain why the conceded point does not undermine the main argument or why it is outweighed by other considerations', 'Reverse the concession by arguing it was not valid after all', 'Present new evidence that was not introduced earlier in the essay', 'Agree with the opposing position and restate the writer\'s thesis unchanged']),
                    ('Qualifiers in argument claims:', ['Limit the scope of the claim to make it more accurate and defensible without eliminating its argumentative force', 'Weaken the argument by suggesting the writer lacks confidence', 'Should be avoided entirely in formal academic writing', 'Apply only to statistical claims, not to value or policy arguments']),
                    ('The AP® Language sophistication point is most often earned by:', ['Genuinely engaging with complexity — considering alternative perspectives, qualifying claims, and acknowledging limitations', 'Using the most sophisticated vocabulary in the essay', 'Including the most quotations from external sources', 'Writing the longest essay response']),
